    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@ernestognw the order in which I was concatenating the v, r, s values to create the signature object was wrong. Hence `ECDSA.recover(bytes32 hash, bytes memory signature) ` was throwing the invalid signature error. \r\nI changed the order of concatenation of v, r, s value to \r\n```solidity\r\n(uint8 v, bytes32 r, bytes32 s) = vm.sign(guardianPK, digest);\r\nbytes memory signature = abi.encodePacked(r, s, v); // note the order here\r\nECDSA.recover(digest, signature); // works well\r\n```",
